Description: SUPPLY CHAINS is a publication devoted to trends and opportunities in old-economy transportation and new-economy technology
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: SUPPLY CHAINS: the place where old-economy transportation meets new-economy technology. In 1869, Leland Stanford drove the Golden Spike into the ground in Utah, creating the first coast-to-coast railroad. The railroads supported billion-dollar modern-dollar fortunes for owners like the Vanderbilts, Carnegies and Flaglers. One century later, in 1956 Malcolm McLean invented containerization, enabling not just modern steamships but also global retail powerhouses like Walmart. Today, we have entered the third wave of value creation. Instead of railroads and steamships, the new-economy supply chain leaders have learned how to harness the power of technology. SUPPLY CHAINS explores this intersection, evaluates the trends, and looks into the future. SUPPLY CHAINS is affiliated with Cambridge Capital, a leading investor in transportation, logistics, and supply chain technology. SUPPLY CHAINS is founded and edited by Benjamin Gordon. Benjamin Gordon has founded several companies in transportation and logistics, and has invested in many supply chain firms as well.
Industry Groups: Education, Information Technology, Internet Services, Transportation

Full Description: We search across many online book retailers to find the lowest prices for a given book. Our company tries to help anyone in need of a book by finding them the cheapest price available online.  Whether a student looking for a textbook, a casual reader looking for a novel, or a programmer looking for a reference book, we provide the user with the ability to search for a particular book that they are interested in, then we find out how much this book costs online.  Along with the book price at various online retailers, we also provide the user with shipping information, coupons, and a link to the book at the given retailer. In addition to providing a destination portal, we also offer a mobile version of the website along with a native iPhone application (Android app on the way as well).  Using these services, a book buyer can be at their local Barnes and Noble or Borders and before buying a book, check it see if it is available cheaper online using their mobile phone.  If they find a better deal on the book online, the user can purchase the book directly on the phone. We are a free service with no annoying ads anywhere on the site.  We founded company as a service for students developed by students and we stick to this motto.  You can search for books by author, title or keyword, and if you know the ISBN number of the book you are interested in, you can search using that as well.  This service will always be free.
